'Tory MPs secretly want Scotland independence for Westminster majority' claims Lord Forsyth
The former Scottish Conservative Secretary claims some Tories believe Scotland could make all the difference in the next election
By Simon Johnson, Scottish Political Editor
11:21AM GMT 04 Nov 2013
Comments
Conservative MPs from the south of England secretly want Scotland to vote for independence to give their party a permanent majority at Westminster, a former Tory Scottish secretary has warned. But Lord Forsyth of Drumlean, said they were “foolish” and expressed frustration at colleagues who want to break up the Union for electoral gain. Sir John Major has also said that the Conservatives would be better off without Scotland, but the UK would suffer. He said: “From a purely political point of view we would be better off without Scotland but the UK would not – the UK needs Scotland it ought to have Scotland.”
With Labour holding 41 seats north of the Border compared to the Tories’ one, Lord Forsyth said some Conservatives believe that Scotland could prove the difference at the next general election. Related Articles
